Cell.Text: As I've told you before I'm a Daughter of Coldharbour... offspring to Molag Bal. | Knowing that Serana shares that blessing with me, I'm already terrified that Harkon will get his hands on her.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05PostValericaInitBranchTopic: When will you return to Tamriel?

Cell.Text: If you think you can accomplish that feat, knowing hundreds before you have tried and failed, then I wish you the best of luck. | But if this miracle were to somehow happen, I would gladly return to Tamriel.
Time is almost irrelevant to the Ideal Masters. | I doubt very much that they'll hasten to exact revenge for freeing me from the ruins.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05PostValericaBranchTopic: Have we angered the Ideal Masters?

Cell.Text: I would gladly accept my fate at their hands if it robs Harkon of victory.

Absolutely. I've spent a great deal of time perfecting an extract that increases the potency of soul husks. | If you wanted to bring some to me, I'd be happy to provide you some of the extract. It should help resist the draining aura of the crystals.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05PostValericaHelpBranchTopic: I could use help with the crystals around here.

Cell.Text: [S] Hmmm, I'd say five of them would be enough.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05PostValericaExtractBranchTopic: I have five soul husks here.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Then I see nothing preventing my return to Tamriel. | Allow me to gather some of my things and I'll head back to Castle Volkihar. | And from the bottom of my heart, I thank you.
I'm sorry, I don't feel comfortable giving them to you. | I understand what you did for Serana and for me, but the prophecy never sat well for me, and I don't want to be a part of it. I'm sorry.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05PostBloodArrowsTopic: Can you give me Bloodcursed Arrows?

Cell.Text: Well, I think it's time I got back to my work as an alchemist. | The Soul Cairn will offer a unique opportunity to continue my studies, and I intend to complete my research. | In the meantime, if there are any potions you might need, feel free to help yourself.

As you've been traveling in the Soul Cairn, your body has become attuned to it. | Let's just say a tiny of you rubbed off on it, and in its place, a bit of the Soul Cairn filled the void. | You should find no difficulty using the portal any longer.

Node.Caption: DLC1VQ05PostValericaRevisitBranchTopic: Will I be able to safely revisit the Soul Cairn?
